    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paddles made from laminated wood covered with rubber on one or two sides. The official Internation Table Tennis Federation term is "racket," but in the the US "paddle" is generally preferred. In European and Asian countries, "bat" may be used. There is no regulation size or shape.</Note_Text>
